description:
Elder Marcus Mason talks about the unprecedented times we are living in and also the central pillar of our faith the Sanctuary Message. Once we realize the times, who is the last generation a most important question for us is how should we as Gods people be living in preparation to see Jesus in peace.

If the video will not play correctly please go to this link
https://www.apocalypseministries.org/aptv/

chapters.title: What Can We Look Forward to the Real Question Is How Shall We Be Living What Should We Be Doing Right Now To Prepare for the Final Event in this Crisis That's Coming We Know that the Last Act of this Drama as as Stated in Testimonies Volume 7 Page 141 Is the National Sunday Law this Is Where We'Re Tending this Is Where We'Re Headed and each Time Events That Have Happened in the Past Have Started or Happened We Have Realized Biblically that We Are Closer to that Time but Now the Things That Are Happening Now Really Say Very Loudly that We Are at the End I Tell People Everywhere I Go Now the End Is Present It Is Not Future

And We'Re Going To Go All the Way Back to Life as Normal and Just Continue On as before Yes the Corona Virus May Come to an End I Suspect at some Point It Will Come to an End but Will We Go Back to Life as Normal Will We Go Back to Just Working and Traveling and Vacationing and Going Back to School as if Nothing Ever Happened and Go On for another 10-15 Years I Do Not Believe so Brothers and Sisters I Believe that We Have Arrived at the End and God's People Need To Be Awake at this Time

The Night Is Far Spent the Day Is at Hand Let Us Therefore Cast Off the Works of Darkness and Let Us Put on the Armor of Light Now Why Do What the Night Is Far Spent the Day Is at Hand but Why Do We Need To Cast Off the Works of Darkness because Now Is Our Salvation Nearer than When We First Believed and It Says Start Off with and Knowing the Time because We Know the Time

God Told It to Him He Spoke to Them Showed It to Them so that They Could Write It They Didn't Come Up with It on Their Own that's Why We Is a More Sure Word We Can Trust It Verse 21 for the Prophecy Came Not in Old Time by the Will of Man's Who Were Just Saying but Holy Men of God Spake as They Were Moved by the Holy Ghost That Means They Spoke and We'Ll Moved under Inspiration of God Therefore When We Read the Prophecies of God's Word Is Sure We Do Well that We Treat It as a Light That Shineth in a Dark Place Now We Are God's Children and if We Have Prophecy We Should Understand What Is Taking Place So if We as God's People Have Prophecies That Have Been Given to It Was in the Bible

We Need To Wear the Shield and the Breastplate and the Sword We Need To Have in Our Hand We Need God To Help Us To Be Prepared To Stand True to Him during these Unprecedented Times because the Coronavirus Is Here the Pandemic Is Worldwide It Is Global and As Long as I Can Remember I'M 47 Years Old and in 47 Years and I Think I'M Safe To Say that Maybe 47 Years before that As Well There Were Has Never Been a Pandemic That Touched the Entire World and Not Just Touched

This First that no Prophecy of the Scripture Is of any Private Interpretation for the Prophecy Came Not in Old Time by the Will of Man but Holy Men of God Spake as They Were Moved by the Holy Ghost so Ordinary Men Wrote Prophecies under Inspiration from God They Didn't Write What They Thought They Wrote under Inspiration That's Why It Is a More Sure Word and Peter Is Saying We Were on the Mount of Transfiguration and What We Saw with Our Own Eyes Prophecy Is More Sure than that

And the Warnings of To Be Prepared That Is a Message of Peace and Safety It Says for When They Shall Say Peace and Safety Then Sudden Destruction Why Is It Then Sudden Destruction because as Two People Remain Asleep as the People Remain in a Condition of Carnal Security or False Security and Arresting Easy Then the Crisis Will Pounce upon Them Which Seemed with no Warning It Says Then Sudden Destruction Shall Come upon Them as a Woman in Travail

We Are Not of the Night nor of Darkness Why because We Are Supposed To Be Children of Prophecy Verse 6 Therefore Let Us Not Sleep as Do Others but Let Us Watch and Be Sober So Let Us Watch and Be Sober so You Can Only Be Sober if You Are Watching the Prophecies Unfold So as We Study God's Word and See What the God Word of God Is Saying and Then We Look about What Is Happening Then that Helps Us Be Sober That Helps Us Not Be So Sleep that We Are Not Preparing that Helps Us To Understand the Urgency of the Hour What We Should Be Doing To Be Prepared To Stand True to God When this Crisis Comes and Why Do I Keep Referring to the Crisis Why Do I Keep Referring to What's Happening because before We Can Ever See Christ Come We'Ve Got To Walk through the Crisis

As Christians We Should Be in Our Communities All the Time We Personally Individually Should Be Touching People and Witnessing to People and Opening God's Word to People but Does that Mean that We Should Not Talk about What's Right in Front of Us Does that Mean that We Should Not Sound the Trumpet with a Certain Sound Does that Mean We Should Be Quiet about What's Happening no We CanNot It Is a Crisis We Must Pick Up the Trumpet and Give It a Certain Sound I Was on a Broadcast Earlier this Morning and I Asked a Question What if We Blew the Trumpet for Lunchtime but There Was a War outside the Walls of Zion

We'Re Going To Be Having Earthquakes and Tornadoes and Tidal Waves and and Volcanoes and Pestilences and Outbreaks and Sickness and and Famines Everything's Going To Be Happening that's that's Been Happening to a Certain Degree but Now We Stack on Top the Distress of Nations with Perplexity and We'Re Going To Look at a Slide Later on that Gives Us Our Good Definition of Perplexity but What that Means Is To Be without Resources To Have no Answer to the Problems That Are Plaguing You
Gordon Brown the Former British Prime Minister Is Calling for the Creation of a Global Government
